                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11267: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-24T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 24, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 24—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>931. Legation’s 920, October 22, 4 p.m. Following from American Consul General at
                    Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“October 23, 4 p.m. Nanking’s October 21, 1 p.m. [<hi rend="italic"
                                >noon?</hi>] It is not possible to telegraph Kian nor has it been
                            possible to do so for past 3 weeks. Outside of Filipino Sister, whose
                            name is not known, no Americans are believed to be there. One American
                            missionary, Miss Ida Lena Weber, whose mission station is at Kian, was
                            in Kiukiang recently. No new developments in Kian situation today except
                            that French Consul states no definite sum fixed for ransom. Lu Ti-ping
                            who is here is leaving for Nanchang tonight.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
